@page "/"
@model EstherLink.Backend.Pages.IndexModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Smart Reverse Gateway for Multi-Network Routing";
    ViewData["DocumentationUrl"] = Model.DocumentationUrl;
}

<section class="relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-cyan-500/20 via-transparent to-slate-900"></div>
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 py-24 relative">
        <p class="uppercase tracking-widest text-cyan-300 text-sm mb-4">OmniRelay</p>
        <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold leading-tight max-w-4xl">Smart Reverse Gateway for Multi-Network Routing</h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-slate-300 max-w-3xl">Expose your private network through a stable VPS gateway and intelligently route outbound traffic across multiple network interfaces.</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-slate-400">Built for developers, DevOps teams, and network engineers.</p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
            <a href="/app/downloads" class="px-6 py-3 rounded-md bg-cyan-500 text-slate-900 font-semibold hover:bg-cyan-400">Download for Windows</a>
            <a href="@Model.DocumentationUrl" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="px-6 py-3 rounded-md border border-slate-700 hover:border-cyan-400">Read Documentation</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 py-16 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10">
    <div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Modern Networks Need Flexible Routing</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4">Many infrastructures rely on multiple internet connections, NAT environments, or networks without static public IPs.</p>
        <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4">Managing access and routing in these environments is often complex, fragile, or requires expensive networking equipment.</p>
        <p class="text-slate-300">OmniRelay solves this problem by creating a smart relay gateway that connects your local network to a VPS and routes traffic intelligently across multiple network interfaces.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-cyan-300">How It Works</h3>
<pre class="text-sm text-slate-200 leading-relaxed whitespace-pre-wrap">Client
   ?
VPS Gateway (Static IP)
   ?
OmniRelay
   +-- IC1 (whitelisted routes)
   +-- IC2 (default routes)
</pre>
        <ol class="mt-6 text-sm text-slate-300 space-y-2 list-decimal list-inside">
            <li>Install OmniRelay on your gateway machine.</li>
            <li>Connect it to your VPS server through an outbound tunnel.</li>
            <li>Define routing policies using CIDR/IP rules.</li>
            <li>Traffic is routed through the correct interface automatically.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Key Features</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <article class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-xl mb-2">Reverse Gateway Connectivity</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300">Connect your internal network to a VPS gateway using outbound tunnels. No static IP required on your local network.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-xl mb-2">Smart Interface Routing</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300">Route traffic across multiple network interfaces based on CIDR/IP policies. Control which ISP or network handles specific destinations.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-xl mb-2">Static Entry Point</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300">Expose services through a stable VPS public IP while keeping infrastructure behind NAT. Perfect for remote access or IP-whitelisted services.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-xl mb-2">CIDR-Based Routing Policies</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300">Define flexible routing rules using CIDR/IP ranges. Direct specific traffic through dedicated network interfaces.</p>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Use Cases</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <article class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900"><h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Remote Infrastructure Access</h3><p class="text-slate-300">Expose internal services through a static gateway without complex firewall configuration.</p></article>
        <article class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900"><h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Multi-ISP Traffic Control</h3><p class="text-slate-300">Control which internet connection handles specific traffic for redundancy and policy management.</p></article>
        <article class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900"><h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">IP Whitelisting</h3><p class="text-slate-300">Provide a stable public IP for services that require strict IP whitelisting.</p></article>
        <article class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900"><h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Secure Network Relay</h3><p class="text-slate-300">Create a controlled gateway between your internal network and external clients.</p></article>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 py-8 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <article class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Product Overview</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300">OmniRelay is designed for environments where traditional VPNs or tunnels are not flexible enough. It acts as a policy-based relay gateway between your infrastructure and the internet.</p>
        <p class="text-slate-300 mt-3">With support for multi-network routing and CIDR-based rules, OmniRelay enables precise control over how traffic flows through your network.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Technical Overview</h2>
        <ul class="text-slate-300 space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Platform: Windows</li>
            <li>Architecture: Reverse relay gateway</li>
            <li>Routing: CIDR/IP-based interface selection</li>
            <li>Gateway: VPS static entry point</li>
            <li>Deployment: Local gateway + VPS</li>
            <li>Control: Desktop UI + service engine</li>
        </ul>
    </article>
</section>

<section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <div class="p-8 rounded-xl border border-cyan-600/40 bg-cyan-500/10">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">OmniRelay License</h2>
        <p class="text-4xl font-bold mt-3">$149 <span class="text-lg text-slate-300">— One-Time Purchase</span></p>
        <ul class="mt-5 text-slate-200 space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Full gateway functionality</li>
            <li>Routing policy engine</li>
            <li>Whitelist CIDR updates</li>
            <li>1 year software updates</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 py-8 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <article class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Quick Start</h2>
        <ol class="text-slate-300 space-y-2 list-decimal list-inside">
            <li>Download OmniRelay.</li>
            <li>Install on your gateway machine.</li>
            <li>Connect to your VPS.</li>
            <li>Configure routing policies.</li>
            <li>Start the relay service.</li>
            <li>Your network gateway is ready.</li>
        </ol>
    </article>
    <article class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Documentation</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300">Learn how to deploy and configure OmniRelay.</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2">
            <li><a class="text-cyan-300 hover:text-cyan-200" target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="@Model.DocumentationUrl">Installation Guide</a></li>
            <li><a class="text-cyan-300 hover:text-cyan-200" target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="@Model.DocumentationUrl">Architecture Overview</a></li>
            <li><a class="text-cyan-300 hover:text-cyan-200" target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="@Model.DocumentationUrl">Configuration Reference</a></li>
            <li><a class="text-cyan-300 hover:text-cyan-200" target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="@Model.DocumentationUrl">Troubleshooting</a></li>
        </ul>
    </article>
</section>

<footer class="border-t border-slate-800 mt-10">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 py-10 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl">OmniRelay</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-400 mt-2">Smart networking gateway for modern infrastructure.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 text-sm">
            <a href="@Model.DocumentationUrl" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="hover:text-cyan-300">Documentation</a>
            <a href="/app/downloads" class="hover:text-cyan-300">Download</a>
            <a href="/app/licenses" class="hover:text-cyan-300">License</a>
            <a href="mailto:contact@omnirelay.local" class="hover:text-cyan-300">Contact</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</footer>